    "headerDoc": "STEP 959 — Combinatorial Number Theory Open Problems\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-21\n\n  Five open problems in combinatorial number theory:\n\n  A. PROUHET-THUE-MORSE AND PAPERFOLDING\n     PTM sequence and its combinatorial properties.\n     New: Subword complexity is 2(n+1) for Thue-Morse (proved by Brlek 1989).\n\n  B. PILLAI CONJECTURE (1936)\n     For fixed a,b,c,d: ax^n - by^m = c has finitely many solutions.\n     Stronger: perfect power gaps → finitely many pairs.\n     Known: Mihailescu 2002 (Catalan: x^p - y^q = 1 has only 3^2-2^3=1).\n\n  C. BUNYAKOVSKY / BATEMAN-HORN CONJECTURE\n     Generalization of Dirich"
